Secondly, one does not get some=\r\nthing without wanting it and putting sufficient effort towards it. One may =\r\nhave deeply desired a Kundalini rise in a previous life and may have put en=\r\nough effort. As a result, one may be getting it now. But one may be unprepa=\r\nred (and ironically may not even want it!) when it comes in this life.\n&gt;&gt; &gt;=\r\n&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;As you do sadhana, try\n not to fancy too many specific\n&gt;&gt; desi=\r\nres. Nature has a delay mechanism in granting your desires (because of cons=\r\ntraints on what Nature can give you right now, arising from YOUR\n&gt;&gt; OWN pre=\r\nvious actions). So Nature sometimes gives you what you want LATE, when you =\r\nno longer want it or want something else. For example, one may pray for gre=\r\nat wealth one&#39;s whole life and be born as a rich but very sick man in next =\r\nlife. One may not enjoy that wealth and pray whole life for health. In the =\r\nlife after that, one may be very healthy, but not have any knowledge or mon=\r\ney. In another \n&gt;&gt; case, one may deeply desire to act in a famous film. One=\r\n may be reborn \n&gt;&gt; as a tiger or a dog and act in a famous film, but not re=\r\nally enjoy that \n&gt;&gt; experience. Basically, people keep going in circles thr=\r\nough various lives, always &quot;seeking&quot; something they are &quot;missing&quot;.\n&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=\r\n=A0\n&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;Anyway, coming back to Kundalini, if one deeply\n desires an out of=\r\n body experience given by a rising Kundalini and one&#39;s previous karmas cons=\r\ntrain one from having it in THIS life, one may be born in next life with th=\r\nis specific desire destined to fructify (if there is enough karmik force be=\r\nhind it).\n&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=\r\n=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt; *\n&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;Kundalini ris=\r\ne is not necessarily scary or painful, if one is well-prepared in terms of =\r\nattitude and detachment.\n&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;Once I saw a chipmunk glued to a =\r\nmouse trap. I went to free it and it panicked so badly and started to shake=\r\n violently. I went to save it from a certain slow death and it was scared t=\r\nhat I would kill it!\n&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;We are like that chipmunk, glued to t=\r\nhe mouse trap called this body-mind complex and scared of being rescued fro=\r\nm a certain slow death!\n&gt;&gt;\n &gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;If our ideas about who we are (vi=\r\nz this current body-mind complex) are incorrect and if we are this &quot;infinit=\r\ne Self&quot; as shastras say, won&#39;t a complete realization of that at some stage=\r\n involve stepping out of this body-mind complex, without being scared?\n&gt;&gt; &gt;=\r\n&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;*=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=\r\n=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0=C2=A0 *\n&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;Kundalini rise after most un=\r\ndesirable conditioning is overcome, is far better than\n&gt;&gt; Kundalini rise fo=\r\nrced when some really undesirable conditioning is still left in one&#39;s syste=\r\nm.\n&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;=C2=A0\n&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;When one transcends one problematic notion about who on=\r\ne is and what one needs, another notion that lay buried deeper in conscious=\r\nness may spring to the surface and torment one. If one overcomes the notion=\r\n &quot;I am the body&quot;, there may be another notion in one&#39;s body-mind complex th=\r\nat one&#39;s\n awareness clings on to (e.g. a great doctor, a great leader, a gr=\r\neat scholar, a great saint etc). As an extreme example, if one person had a=\r\n hidden deep desire to be a great soul who rescues the world, he may fancy =\r\nthat he is a re-incarnated X or Y who will rescue the world now. When one&#39;s=\r\n self-awareness (i.e. Kundalini!) deeply clings to any such notio