, means that the scope for misunderstanding is tremendous.&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;=\r\nEverybody wants happiness but most are unable to realise that &quot;material obj=\r\nects&quot; won&#39;t make you happy.&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;That&#39;s li=\r\nfe for you. See all the saints. You are unlikely to see even one who lived =\r\na life of enjoyment, in fact they all lived lives of misery(when looked at =\r\nby an external observer). However the internal joy of Kundalini is somethin=\r\ng which fills that saint so completely that some great ones were completely=\r\n unaware of their external problems.&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;When Kundalini (Chit Shakt=\r\ni) awakens it puts the external world to sleep.I sometimes&nbsp;compare Kun=\r\ndalini rise to a baby being thrown in the air by the parent. The baby&#39;s loo=\r\nk of joy is tremendous because the baby&#39;s surrender is complete. The baby k=\r\nnows that it can&#39;t do anything without the mother so it&#39;s feeling is that o=\r\nf\n joy.&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;The problem with adults is that they have to learn surr=\r\nender. This surrendering of ego to the Divine Mother takes time and is not =\r\na painless process unlike that of the baby.&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;That results in the=\r\n problem that &quot;real&nbsp;surges&quot; of energy may&nbsp;result&nbsp;in mental h=\r\navoc.&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;Secondly, many people who=\r\n have Kundalini rise are brought up with the concept of japa. Japa which de=\r\nals with the Air element which is unstable anyway can cause serious instabi=\r\nlity in these people.&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;Some&nbsp;of the&nbsp;people who have Kun=\r\ndalini &quot;rises&quot; may be people who may feel that they haven&#39;t done a single w=\r\northwhile thing in their lives and think that the faking of Kundalini rises=\r\n may help them get some esteem in the eye of the general public.&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&=\r\ngt; &gt;Coming to the specific problem:In general, for any doctor, the sepa=\r\nration of the true from the false claims must precede any attempt at\n helpi=\r\nng the patient. A true Kundalini rise needs niyama to finish Vata. Vata ten=\r\nds to like irregularity, in food habits, sleeping habits, sexual matters, t=\r\nravel.&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;To finish Vata, all&nbsp;that must be regimentalis=\r\ned, then appropriate herbs used. Control of Apana is essential as is Bramha=\r\ncharya. Application of oils to the body to totally calm Vata may be useful.=\r\n I suppose even Shiro basti in difficult real cases may be useful.&lt;br&gt;&gt; =\r\n&gt;Then institute small&nbsp;Homas to MahaGanapati and the nava grahas to =\r\nbe performed by the patient. That should really improve matters, as Ganesha=\r\n is The Lord of the Muladhara.&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;The whole process may be chalked=\r\n out over one-two years.&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;In pure non real cases, just psychothe=\r\nrapy may be sufficient.&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;Jai Shree Ram=\r\na&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;Jai Shree Rama&lt;br&gt;&gt;=\r\n &gt;&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;On Friday, March 1, 2013, Narasimha P.V.R.\n Rao wrote:&lt;br=\r\n&gt;&gt; &gt;&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;Namaste friends,&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;=\r\n&gt;Someone with psychiatric problems may expereience what sounds like a Ku=\r\nndalini rise, but it may or may not be one.&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&gt; =\r\n&gt;&gt;It must be conceded though that Kundalini spontaneously rising thro=\r\nugh various nadis without one having gone through proper preparation in thi=\r\ns life (i.e. fine-tuning of one&#39;s attitude and development of detachment) C=\r\nAN create havoc!&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;One may wonder how =\r\nKundalini may spontaneously rise in a layman with no sadhana, while many se=\r\nrious sadhakas may not experience it.&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;&g=\r\nt;Firstly, Kundalini rise is NOT an achievement. It is just A SMALL&lt;br&gt;&gt;=\r\n STEP in overcoming one&#39;s current limited identity.&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;=\r\nbr&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;Let me give an analogy. One wanting to move from one&#39;s smal=\r\nl dilapidated house (this&lt;br&gt;&gt; body-mind complex)\n to a huge palace (rea=\r\nlized Self) may first construct the palace over time and move into it when =\r\nit is COMPLETE. Alternately, if one occasionally goes and stays in the pala=\r\nce still under construction (analogy for out of body experiences due to Kun=\r\ndalini rise), is it an achievement? In fact, it comes with risks. The forme=\r\nr approach is safer and one loses nothing in it. Similarly, one can progres=\r\ns towards complete Self-realization without any out of body experiences. Th=\r\nese are not my word&#39;s, but Maharshi Vasishtha&#39;s words to Lord Rama.&lt;br&gt;&gt;=\r\n &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;Secondly, one does not get something withou=\r\nt wanting it and putting sufficient effort towards it. One may have deeply =\r\ndesired a Kundalini rise in a previous life and may have put enough effort.=\r\n As a result, one may be getting it now. But one may be unprepared (and iro=\r\nnically may not even want it!) when it comes in this life.&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;=\r\n&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;As you do sadhana, try\n not to fancy too many specif=\r\nic&lt;br&gt;&gt; desires. Nature has a delay mechanism in granting your desires (=\r\nbecause of constraints on what Nature can give you right now, arising from =\r\nYOUR&lt;br&gt;&gt; OWN previous actions). So Nature sometimes gives you what you =\r\nwant LATE, when you no longer want it or want something else. For example, =\r\none may pray for great wealth one&#39;s whole life and be born as a rich but ve=\r\nry sick man in next life. One may not enjoy that wealth and pray whole life=\r\n for health. In the life after that, one may be very healthy, but not have =\r\nany knowledge or money. In another &lt;br&gt;&gt; case, one may deeply desire to =\r\nact in a famous film. One may be reborn &lt;br&gt;&gt; as a tiger or a dog and ac=\r\nt in a famous film, but not really enjoy that &lt;br&gt;&gt; experience. Basicall=\r\ny, people keep going in circles through various lives, always &quot;seeking&quot; som=\r\nething they are &quot;missing&quot;.&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;Anyway, c=\r\noming back to Kundalini, if one deeply\n desires an out of body experience g=\r\niven by a rising Kundalini and one&#39;s previous karmas constrain one from hav=\r\ning it in THIS life, one may be born in next life with this specific desire=\r\n destined to fructify (if there is enough karmik force behind it).&lt;br&gt;&gt; =\r\n&gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; =\r\n*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&gt; *&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp=\r\n;&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;Kundalini rise is not necessarily scary or painful, if on=\r\ne is well-prepared in terms of attitude and detachment.&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&nb=\r\nsp;&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;Once I saw a chipmunk glued to a mouse trap. I went to =\r\nfree it and it panicked so badly and started to shake violently. I went to =\r\nsave it from a certain slow death and it was scared that I would kill it!&lt;b=\r\nr&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;We are like that chipmunk, glued to t=\r\nhe mouse trap called this body-mind complex and scared of being rescued fro=\r\nm a certain slow death!&lt;br&gt;&gt;\n &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;If our idea=\r\ns about who we are (viz this current body-mind complex) are incorrect and i=\r\nf we are this &quot;infinite Self&quot; as shastras say, won&#39;t a complete realization=\r\n of that at some stage involve stepping out of this body-mind complex, with=\r\nout being scared?&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp=\r\n;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&lt;br&gt;=\r\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;Kundalini rise after most undesirable c=\r\nonditioning is overcome, is far better than&lt;br&gt;&gt; Kundalini rise forced w=\r\nhen some really undesirable conditioning is still left in one&#39;s system.&lt;br&gt;=\r\n&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;When one transcends one problematic not=\r\nion about who one is and what one needs, another notion that lay buried dee=\r\nper in consciousness may spring to the surface and torment one. If one over=\r\ncomes the notion &quot;I am the body&quot;, there may be another notion in one&#39;s body=\r\n-mind complex that one&#39;s\n awareness clings on to (e.g. a great doctor, a gr=\r\neat leader, a great scholar, a great saint etc). As an extreme example, if =\r\none person had a hidden deep desire to be a great soul who rescues the worl=\r\nd, he may fancy that he is a re-incarnated X or Y who will rescue the world=\r\n now. When one&#39;s self-awareness (i.e. Kundalini!) deeply clings to any such=\r\n notion, it can cause havoc. The person may show some signs of progress and=\r\n yet remain in ignorance and get stuck badly.&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&gt=\r\n; &gt;&gt;An awakened Kundalini in a system with undesirable conditioning m=\r\nay accentuate one&#39;s weaknesses and wrong notions heavily and cause serious =\r\npsychiatric and spiritual problems.&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;=\r\n*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;=\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp; *&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;The best approach I r=\r\necommend is to NOT think in terms of Kundalini and its rise. Just do sadhan=\r\na, overcome\n your&lt;br&gt;&gt; weaknesses and improve your detachment over time.=\r\n Again, I want to emphasize that detachment is not disgust or distaste for =\r\nlife/things/people around you. Disgust is the other side of coin of attachm=\r\nent. It is a negative attachment.&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&lt;b=\r\nr&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;Don&#39;t worry about &lt;br&gt;&gt; whether your Kundalini rises or n=\r\not. Worry about whether you are able to resist 6 internal enemies (shadripu=\r\ns) and 8 bondages (ashta pashas) or &lt;br&gt;&gt; not. If your ability to resist=\r\n them is increasing, you are making progress. EVEN IF your Kundalini is fas=\r\nt asleep, you are still making progress. When you completely overcome them,=\r\n Kundalini (your self-awareness) &lt;br&gt;&gt; will automatically ascend to the =\r\ntop and meet Her Lord (true Self).&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;*=\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&=\r\nnbsp;&nbsp; *&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;One word on surrenderi=\r\nng to\n a personal deity. Though true surrender is helpful, most people do n=\r\not have it. They simply do business with god. Though people may be offended=\r\n by my words, this is the plain and bare fact.&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&g=\r\nt; &gt;&gt;&quot;I want X, I will pray to you and please give it to me&quot;, &quot;I am s=\r\ncared of Kundalini rise, I will pray to you and please protect me&quot; - all th=\r\nis is just a business deal. There is something you want and you ask god for=\r\n it. True surrender has no place for agendas, desires, demands or expectati=\r\nons. True surrender is losing oneself in one&#39;s fascination for the qualitie=\r\ns of Lord. True surrender is accepting anything Lord throws one&#39;s way (whet=\r\nher it is pleasurable or highly painful) as Lord&#39;s prasad and accepting it =\r\ngratefully. True surrender is thinking of Lord with fascination and pleasur=\r\ne, even in the face of (and during) Death.&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&gt; &=\r\ngt;&gt;If one without true surrender and with many desires and wrong\n notio=\r\nns experiences a Kundalini rise, one may still be trapped, despite thinking=\r\n of a personal god. It is not that god does not want to &quot;protect&quot; one as sa=\r\nid below. It is not about protecting or endangering. If you go back to my &quot;=\r\nchipmunk glued to mouse trap&quot; example above, I was trying to protect it, bu=\r\nt it was scared. Similarly, one&#39;s conditioning makes one *run away* from Go=\r\nd&#39;s&lt;br&gt;&gt; protection! God&#39;s protection may seem to a conditioned mind lik=\r\ne grave danger that one should run away from!&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&gt=\r\n; &gt;&gt;*&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&n=\r\nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; *&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;Whether thr=\r\nough the path of wisdom or surrender, develop dispassion and detachment. Re=\r\nalize that all this is temporary and can be taken away anytime. Enjoy it wh=\r\nile you have and keep doing your best, but be prepared to lose everything a=\r\nnytime. Only detachment and a very light mental conditioning\n (very light d=\r\nesires, dislikes etc) can protect one as one&#39;s Kundalini rises to meet True=\r\n Self. Heavy conditioning and impurities in one&#39;s nadis will distract risin=\r\ng Kundalini (self-awareness) and stop Her from meeting True Self.&lt;br&gt;&gt; &=\r\ngt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;The real key is how light your conditioning i=\r\ns.&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;Best regards,&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;Nar=\r\nasimha&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;--------&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;Astrology &amp; Spiritualit=\r\ny Resources: &lt;a href=3D&quot;&quot; rel=3D&quot;nofollow&quot; target=3D&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;http://www.ved=\r\nicastrologer.org/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;--------&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt=\r\n;&gt;&nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;&gt;&gt;_________=\r\n_______________________&lt;br&gt;&gt; &gt;